Welcome to honk - a modern pure-Go RISC-V 64 operating system.

This file lives in the immutable, embedded core image (read-only). Files you
write with `cp` land in the persistent kv store, which shadows the core in the
overlay filesystem.

The kv store keeps small values in memory and spills larger ones (like this
message) to disk, so the store is not bounded by RAM; `cp motd readme` therefore
exercises the disk-resident value path, and the copy survives a reboot.
